  "doc_id": "50159",
  "text": "Students who had SPSS on their home computer (n = 73) intended to attend more virtual tutorials (M = 3.92, SEM = 0.50) than those who did not (n = 38; M = 2.61, SEM = 0.28), t (109) = -2.23, p = .028, d = 0.47. This represents a small effect size according to [CITATION_1] . Higher engagement in critical thinking and use of peer learning were also associated with greater intentions to attend the virtual tutorials. Thus, students who engaged in deeper processing of material and who recognised the importance of peer discussion and interaction to their learning, as well as those who had the technology required to do this at home, had stronger intentions to attend this tutorial option.",
